 by greater awareness of environmental sustainability. Manufacturers are responding to this demand by developing deodorants and perfumes specifically tailored for men's skin types and scent preferences, incorporating essential oils and other plant-based ingredients to create products that align with their values of health and wellness.</p><p>In contrast, the Women’s segment in the natural deodorants and perfumes market is characterized by a long-standing preference for eco-friendly and organic personal care products. Women have been at the forefront of the natural products movement, driven by concerns over skin sensitivity, allergies, and the long-term effects of exposure to chemicals found in traditional deodorants and perfumes. As a result, women are increasingly choosing products with natural ingredients such as baking soda, arrowroot powder, and essential oils that provide effective odor control without the risk of harmful side effects. The women’s segment of the market also shows a strong inclination toward fragrances that are floral, citrusy, or herbal, as these scents are perceived as more feminine and gentle. Many women are also drawn to brands that emphasize sustainability, cruelty-free practices, and environmentally conscious packaging, as they tend to be more aligned with their personal values. As the demand for safe, non-toxic, and environmentally friendly personal care products continues to grow, the women’s segment remains a significant driver in the overall natural deodorants and perfumes market.</p><p>The Unisex segment in the natural deodorants and perfumes market reflects a growing trend toward gender-neutral and inclusive beauty products. Unisex products are gaining traction as consumers increasingly reject rigid gender stereotypes in personal care. The demand for unisex natural deodorants and perfumes is driven by the appeal of fragrances that are not overly floral or musky but strike a balance that can be enjoyed by anyone. These products often 